        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(76, "p");
        i0.ɵɵtext(77, " 26. Waving down the bus for it to stop \u2014 In large cities in Europe or North America, buses stop at all stops. Here, if we don't wave the bus down, we run the risk of missing the ride we've been waiting for for a long time. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(78, "p");
        i0.ɵɵtext(79, " 27. Our high number of holidays \u2014 In all, we have 12 national holidays, not counting those decreed by states and municipalities and those dedicated to certain professional categories, such as Teacher's Day. For some foreigners, it's a mess. Other countries, such as Colombia and India, however, are more \u201Clazy\u201D and have 18 holidays a year.\u200B ");
